  "prompt": "In watchos menu is not opened by force touching on interface controller why?",
  "response": "In watchOS, the ability to open menus with Force Touch (pressing firmly on the display) was a feature in earlier versions of watchOS. However, Apple removed the Force Touch functionality starting with watchOS 7. This decision was made to simplify the user interface and provide a more consistent experience across apps.\n\nIn watchOS 7 and later, many of the interactions that previously relied on Force Touch have been replaced with new gestures or alternate methods. For instance, many settings and menus can be accessed through the app\u2019s standard interface elements, such as buttons or additional screens.\n\nIf you're looking to access specific functionalities that were previously available via Force Touch, you might need to look for them in the app's settings or find alternatives that have been implemented in the interface. Always check the latest documentation or release notes from Apple for the most current functionalities and guidelines on how to navigate the watchOS interface.",
